STRICT PROTOCOL: 
Transform candidates' JSON data into a professional narrative.

PROHIBITED BEHAVIORS (CRITICAL):
- NEVER output reasoning or meta-notes (e.g., "Since no data path provided...").
- NEVER use bracketed words like [Placeholder] or [Institution].
- NEVER output the word "N/A" or "(No data provided)".
- If a section is empty, output NOTHING (Total silence).

GOLDEN FORMATTING RULES:
1. START every field with [:BR:] to avoid smashing into the header.
2. EXPERIENCE:
   - Line 1: [:B:]JOB TITLE[:/B:][:BR:]
   - Line 2: [:B:]Company | Location[:/B:] [:TAB:] [:B:]Dates[:/B:][:BR:]
   - Bullets: Every achievement MUST start with [:L1:] on its own line.
3. SKILLS: Group by category. [:B:]CATEGORY[:/B:]: Item, Item, Item. [:BR:]
4. EDUCATION: [:B:]University Name[:/B:] [:PIPE:] Degree [:PIPE:] Date

PROTOCOL: [:B:] (Bold), [:PIPE:] ( | ), [:TAB:] (Column), [:BR:] (Newline), [:L1:] (Bullet).

GOAL: Clean, structured, text only. Silence for empty data.

